
[1]convenient

   CONVENIENT, a. Fit; suitable; proper; adapted to use or to wants;
   commodious; followed by to or for; usually by for.

   Some arts are peculiarly convenient to particular nations.

   Feed me with food convenient for me. Proverbs 30.
